  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Chairman Personal Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role</strong></p><p>We are looking for a highly reliable and resourceful <strong>Personal Assistant</strong> to support the Chairman. This role requires a professional working attitude, who can seamlessly manage business and personal matters, coordinate with global stakeholders, and travel internationally at short notice.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p><strong>Executive & Administrative Support</strong></p><ul><li>Provide full spectrum administrative and personal support to the Chairman, including calendar management, travel planning, and daily coordination.</li><li>Accompany the Chairman on overseas business trips and personal travel, ensuring smooth logistics, accommodation, and schedule management.</li><li>Act as a gatekeeper and liaison with internal teams, business partners, and external stakeholders across different time zones.</li><li>Draft, translate, and review correspondence, documents, and presentations in both English and Chinese.</li><li>Organize and support meetings, prepare agendas, record minutes, and follow up on action points.</li><li>Handle confidential and sensitive matters with absolute discretion and professionalism.</li></ul><p><strong>Lifestyle & Family Support</strong></p><ul><li>Manage lifestyle-related arrangements such as dining, events, entertainment, and leisure activities.</li><li>Oversee family-related logistics including schooling, healthcare, household staff coordination, and travel planning.</li><li>Assist with property management, luxury services, and special projects as required.</li><li>Support in organizing private functions, hosting VIP guests, and handling personal errands.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree or diploma preferred; strong language, business, or hospitality background an advantage.</li><li>Proven experience as a Personal Assistant / Executive Assistant to C-level executives, entrepreneurs, or in a family office environment.</li><li>Strong organizational skills with the ability to anticipate needs, prioritize tasks, and manage multiple projects.</li><li>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, with cultural sensitivity.</li><li>Flexible and willing to travel internationally, sometimes on short notice.</li><li>High level of integrity, discretion, and commitment to confidentiality.</li><li>Tech-savvy with proficiency in MS Office and mobile productivity tools.</li></ul>",
